annotationSettings.title: Annotation Settings
annotationSettings.showAllZones.desc: Always show zones on frames where objects have entered a zone.

offset.label: Annotation Offset
offset.desc: This data comes from your camera's detect feed but is overlayed on images from the the record feed. It is unlikely that the two streams are perfectly in sync. As a result, the bounding box and the footage will not line up perfectly. However, the annotation_offset field can be used to adjust this.
offset.millisecondsToOffset: Milliseconds to offset detect annotations by. Default: 0
offset.tips: TIP: Imagine there is an event clip with a person walking from left to right. If the event timeline bounding box is consistently to the left of the person then the value should be decreased. Similarly, if a person is walking from left to right and the bounding box is consistently ahead of the person then the value should be increased.
